Dialogue: 1,0:03:51.54,0:03:57.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,以今天的技术 飞机全自动起飞着陆是完全可能的
Dialogue: 2,0:03:51.54,0:03:57.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,With today's technology, an aircraft capable of taking off and landing all by itself is definitely possible.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:57.94,0:04:02.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,但让全自动的飞机像飞行员那样安全地处理各种无法预料的情景还很困难
Dialogue: 2,0:03:57.94,0:04:02.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,But getting a fully automated aircraft to deal with every unexpected scenario
Dialogue: 1,0:04:02.25,0:04:06.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,但让全自动的飞机像飞行员那样安全地处理各种无法预料的情景还很困难
Dialogue: 2,0:04:02.25,0:04:06.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,whilst still being as safe as a pilot is way more difficult.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:06.34,0:04:09.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,更不用提如今民航基建如此完善
Dialogue: 2,0:04:06.34,0:04:09.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,Not to mention that our airline infrastructure is so developed,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:09.48,0:04:11.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,想要完全把飞行员替换下去
Dialogue: 2,0:04:09.48,0:04:11.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,that in order to replace the pilot completely,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:11.97,0:04:16.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,飞机还要能自动在停机位与跑道之间滑行
Dialogue: 2,0:04:11.97,0:04:16.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,each airplane would need to be able to taxi between the gate and the runway,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:16.44,0:04:19.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,全程需要保持和机场其他飞机的通信
Dialogue: 2,0:04:16.44,0:04:19.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,all whilst communicating with every other plane at the airport.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:20.21,0:04:26.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,说白了 如果波音明天出了一款全新的无飞行员的飞机 那FAA肯定懵逼了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:20.21,0:04:26.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,To put it simply, if Boeing came out tomorrow with their new pilotless airliner, the FAA would lose their minds.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:27.42,0:04:31.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,额滴娘啊 自动飞行员漏气了！
Dialogue: 2,0:04:27.42,0:04:31.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,Oh my God! The automatic pilot, it's deflating!
Dialogue: 1,0:04:31.52,0:04:37.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,而航天飞行从一开始 火箭就一直是靠自己的制导系统
Dialogue: 2,0:04:31.52,0:04:37.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since the beginning of spaceflight, rockets have always operated under their own guidance systems.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:37.34,0:04:39.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,应付如此高空高速的情况
Dialogue: 2,0:04:37.34,0:04:39.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,When dealing with such high speeds and altitudes,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:39.56,0:04:44.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,计算机控制的火箭能比任何人类控制的入轨更加精确
Dialogue: 2,0:04:39.56,0:04:44.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,computers are able to guide the rocket into orbit with much more precision than a human ever could.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:45.36,0:04:51.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,自动化系统用在猎鹰九号的着陆上则有更加明显的优势
Dialogue: 2,0:04:45.36,0:04:51.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,The advantage that automated systems provide is even more clear when we look at the landing of the Falcon 9.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:51.68,0:04:56.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为火箭着陆时推重比始终大于1
Dialogue: 2,0:04:51.68,0:04:56.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since the rocket has a thrust to weight ratio higher than 1 during a landing,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:56.24,0:04:58.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,使得它必须执行一次"suicide burn"
Dialogue: 2,0:04:56.24,0:04:58.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,it has to perform a "suicide burn"
Dialogue: 1,0:04:58.33,0:05:02.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,即在最后某一刻让发动机点火
Dialogue: 2,0:04:58.33,0:05:02.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,which involves firing the engines at the last possible second.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:02.34,0:05:06.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,发动机开早了 火箭会在还没到地面的时候就停下来
Dialogue: 2,0:05:02.34,0:05:06.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,Turn on the engines too soon and the rocket will slow down before reaching the ground.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:06.85,0:05:11.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,发动机开晚了 火箭又没有足够时间减速
Dialogue: 2,0:05:06.85,0:05:11.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,Turn on the engines too late and the rocket won't be able to slow down in time.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:12.08,0:05:17.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,在火箭着陆时 其计算机会根据其高度和速度
Dialogue: 2,0:05:12.08,0:05:17.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,As the rocket comes in, its onboard computers are constantly measuring its altitude and its speed,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:17.48,0:05:19.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,实时解算发动机点火时间
Dialogue: 2,0:05:17.48,0:05:19.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,to work out when to light the engines.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:20.09,0:05:22.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,在完美的时间点火
Dialogue: 2,0:05:20.09,0:05:22.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,Getting the timing absolutely perfect
Dialogue: 1,0:05:22.14,0:05:25.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,就好比在倒计时刚好到0.00的时候暂停这个视频一样
Dialogue: 2,0:05:22.14,0:05:25.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,is like trying to pause this video when the number reaches zero.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:26.02,0:05:27.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,人类是几乎做不到的
Dialogue: 2,0:05:26.02,0:05:27.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,You can't.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:28.37,0:05:31.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然猎鹰九号可以以惊人的精度着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:05:28.37,0:05:31.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,Although the Falcon 9 is able to land with incredible accuracy,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:31.86,0:05:37.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,但这高度依赖GPS的精确定位来预测落点
Dialogue: 2,0:05:31.86,0:05:37.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,it relies largely on GPS to precisely guide it to a predetermined landing spot.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:37.92,0:05:41.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,这在未来火星任务中是无法做到的
Dialogue: 2,0:05:37.92,0:05:41.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is something that won't be possible for future missions to Mars,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:41.14,0:05:46.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为目前火星上没有GPS支持其完成定点精确着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:05:41.14,0:05:46.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,since there is no current GPS system around the planet to provide pinpoint accuracy.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:46.98,0:05:53.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,到了2022年 太空叉打算使用新的Starship火箭执行火星货运任务
Dialogue: 2,0:05:46.98,0:05:53.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,In 2022, SpaceX plans to send a cargo mission to Mars using their new Starship rocket.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:53.64,0:05:58.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,在未来 太空叉有可能会在火星表面建设着陆场
Dialogue: 2,0:05:53.64,0:05:58.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,In the future, it's possible that SpaceX could build landing pads on the Martian surface
Dialogue: 1,0:05:58.72,0:06:03.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,并为火星GPS发射卫星星座
Dialogue: 2,0:05:58.72,0:06:03.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,and operate a constellation of satellites to give Mars its own GPS.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:03.74,0:06:08.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,但在最初几次任务中 Starship需要能够自行实时分析地形
Dialogue: 2,0:06:03.74,0:06:08.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,But for the first couple of missions, Starship will need to analyze the terrain in real time
Dialogue: 1,0:06:08.65,0:06:11.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,选择一个合适的着陆点
Dialogue: 2,0:06:08.65,0:06:11.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,and choose a suitable landing spot all by itself.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:12.10,0:06:17.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,这就是少有的 人类比计算机更有用的场景之一
Dialogue: 2,0:06:12.10,0:06:17.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is one of the few situations where human input is more valuable than a computer.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:17.22,0:06:19.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,在阿波罗11号着陆过程中
Dialogue: 2,0:06:17.22,0:06:19.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,During the landing of Apollo 11,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:19.17,0:06:23.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,机载计算机引导登月舱飞往一块充满巨石的区域
Dialogue: 2,0:06:19.17,0:06:23.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,the onboard computers were taking the Lunar Module towards a field of boulders.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:23.70,0:06:26.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为计算机没有意识到潜在的危险
Dialogue: 2,0:06:23.70,0:06:26.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since the computers were unaware of the possible danger,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:26.48,0:06:31.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,尼尔·阿姆斯特朗接管了登月舱的控制 引导其着陆在一块更平整的月面上
Dialogue: 2,0:06:26.48,0:06:31.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Neil Armstrong had to take control of the Lunar Module and direct it towards a clear patch of ground.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:32.33,0:06:36.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,对于Starship着陆火星来说 它可能会有自己的人工智能视角
Dialogue: 2,0:06:32.33,0:06:36.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,For Starship landing on Mars, it could have its own artificial vision,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:36.09,0:06:41.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,利用多个训练后的箭载相机避开复杂地形 让飞船着陆在平整的火星表面
Dialogue: 2,0:06:36.09,0:06:41.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,with multiple onboard cameras trained to avoid rough terrain and land the spacecraft on flat ground.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:42.45,0:06:48.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,另一个建议解决方案是在着陆区附近事先放下几个小型应答机
Dialogue: 2,0:06:42.45,0:06:48.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,Another solution that many have suggested is to land a series of small transponders near the landing site
Dialogue: 1,0:06:48.17,0:06:50.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,创造一个局部的导航系统
Dialogue: 2,0:06:48.17,0:06:50.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,to create a localised GPS.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:50.72,0:06:55.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,保证其中至少三个能和Starship通信
Dialogue: 2,0:06:50.72,0:06:55.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,At least three of these would be able to communicate with Starship and accurately plot its position,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:55.85,0:06:57.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,引导其在着陆场精确着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:06:55.85,0:06:57.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,guiding it towards the landing site.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:58.46,0:07:03.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,无论哪种方法 Starship的首次火星着陆都将是一次极为困难且令人兴奋的事件
Dialogue: 2,0:06:58.46,0:07:03.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,Either way, the first Starship landing on Mars will be an incredibly tense but exciting event!
Dialogue: 1,0:07:04.40,0:07:09.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,另一个令人兴奋的事情是Audible提供的海量的有声书
Dialogue: 2,0:07:04.40,0:07:09.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,Another thing that's exciting is the incredible range of audio books that Audible has to offer.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:10.21,0:07:15.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,Audible有独一无二的 各种能想象到的领域的有声书
Dialogue: 2,0:07:10.21,0:07:15.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,Audible has an unmatched selection of audio books covering every topic imaginable.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:15.26,0:07:21.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们甚至还有关于X-15计划的有声书 里面有参与此计划的先驱的访谈
Dialogue: 2,0:07:15.26,0:07:21.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,They even have an audio book all about the X-15 program with interviews from the pioneers that made it happen.
